<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Sullosar</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-08 17:08:21</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Allrighty, here's a few basics on the quest for you.  I have done it a couple times, and I can solo the mobs at lvl 22 and get good exp.  Slaythe is in misty thicket, his spawn is triggered by asking Broning Higginsbot "what small favor?"  Faldor is a bit more complicated.  He spawns in the black crows tavern in qeynos, in the back room with the fake wall.  His placeholder is a beggar.  Now, here's where it gets tricky.  You have to kill the beggar, then that will trigger Faldor's spawn Exactly 2 Hours Later.  So, feel free to go do something else, just come back before the 2 hours are up and hope someone else isn't there camping him.  In my opinion, no, you can't tell the person "excuse me, I killed the bandit 2 hours ago, so this spawn belongs to me" since they were there first and you left, but that's just my 2 cents.  This quest is great for someone lvl 22 or so, and you get a cool axe out of it too.<BR>
<BR>
Sullosar<BR>
Lvl 22 Ranger of Tunare<BR>
Bronze Dragon Fellowship</font></td></tr></table>
